{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Additional failure mode (same review-plan subsystem): during this run, review-plan's attested-mode git handling (git fetch/stash to compute the signature at HEAD) FAILED mid-operation (the 'cannot lock ref refs/remotes/origin/tickets' race under 4 parallel reviews) and left a stray stash APPLIED into the working tree, injecting <<<<<<< / ======= / >>>>>>> merge-conflict markers into 4 unrelated core files (src/rebar/config.py, src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py, src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py, infra/gerrit/materialize-g2p-config.sh). This BROKE the working tree (rebar failed to import; all tests errored at collection) until manually resolved via git checkout HEAD. review-plan must (a) never run concurrently in the same worktree without a lock, and (b) guarantee working-tree restoration is atomic / rolled back on failure — a fail-closed abort must not leave a half-applied stash. AC candidate: review-plan git handling is crash-safe (no working-tree mutation survives a failed run)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783885744430223001,"uuid":"31679807-4067-4328-826a-7d816ca6c396"}